  "response": "There are several FDA-approved medications to treat erectile dysfunction (ED):\n\n1. Oral Medications (PDE5 inhibitors):\n- Sildenafil (Viagra)\n- Tadalafil (Cialis)\n- Vardenafil (Levitra)\n- Avanafil (Stendra)\n\n2. Each medication works slightly differently, with varying:\n- Onset time\n- Duration of effectiveness\n- Side effects\n\n3. The \"best\" medicine depends on individual factors:\n- Overall health\n- Underlying conditions\n- Potential drug interactions\n- Personal response to medication\n- Side effect tolerance\n\n4. Consulting a healthcare professional is crucial to:\n- Determine the most suitable medication\n- Check for potential contraindications\n- Discuss dosage\n- Address underlying health issues\n\n5. Non-pharmaceutical treatments include:\n- Lifestyle changes\n- Counseling\n- Exercise\n- Diet modifications\n\nAlways consult a doctor to get personalized medical advice tailored to your specific health needs and medical history.",
